<div id="review_2126899135" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2126899135" />
    <a title="Cphe" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14907696-cphe"><img alt="Cphe" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1378006896p2/14907696.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2126899135?book_show_action=true">Jan 10, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cphe" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cphe" href="/user/show/14907696-cphe">Cphe</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25822712-zeno-s-conscience">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=historical">historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=psychological">psychological</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=self-help">self-help</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=obsession">obsession</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=2018">2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=defies-a-genre">defies-a-genre</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=guardian-boxall-2018">guardian-boxall-2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14907696-cphe?shelf=humour">humour</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2126899135" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14402041846025991214">A friend on GR&apos;s brought this to my attention. It wasn&apos;t a novel I&apos;d previously come across. Will admit that it was also a novel that I nearly put aside because I couldn&apos;t quite &quot;gel&quot; with Zeno, his thoughts, various ailments, neurotic disposition or his indecisiveness to say the least. Zeno was an unreliable narrator, however it was his story to tell and to psychoanalyse.<br/><br/>Having said that Zeno did grow on me and I quite enjoyed reading his thoughts and seeing life through Zeno&apos;s eyes.<br/><br/>Thoroughly </span>
  <span id="freeText14402041846025991214" style="display:none">A friend on GR's brought this to my attention. It wasn't a novel I'd previously come across. Will admit that it was also a novel that I nearly put aside because I couldn't quite "gel" with Zeno, his thoughts, various ailments, neurotic disposition or his indecisiveness to say the least. Zeno was an unreliable narrator, however it was his story to tell and to psychoanalyse.<br /><br />Having said that Zeno did grow on me and I quite enjoyed reading his thoughts and seeing life through Zeno's eyes.<br /><br />Thoroughly enjoyed the foreword by Elizabeth Hardwick. Having delved into James Joyce last year I was surprised and intrigued to find that Joyce and the author were well known to each other and that Joyce had been instrumental in promoting this novel at the time.<br /><br />Well worth a look at.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14402041846025991214" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


